                "href": "/profile/Annie-Dellaine"
            },
            "answer_text": "Yes and no. Members of BTS, especially RM and Suga, and JHope in early albums, are listed among writers for almost all BTS songs. So BTS somewhat participates in writing most of their songs, along with many other artists per song, some of which are Pdogg, Supreme Boi,\u2026 Now, since I've noticed many Armys praise this as why BTS is successful I.e. why they listen to them, let me clarify that they do not write lyrics by themselves, they merely participate in writing. The amount of contribution to song is relative as it may have some to no impact to the song. To make songs seen more relatable (and idols more talented), sometimes idols tend to be featured as writers, with no explanation how much of their participation actually affected final song. The similar situation is e.g. RM writing his Unicef speech - he didn't. But to make it more relatable, it is said RM made a draft and agency finished it - you can't tell how much of it was RM and how much others. Because Armys idolize RM and speech seems more personal written by RM a not some professional speech writer, they choose to claim that agency merely did grammar correction (its hilarious anyone actually believes this). The same thing is with songs. One or more members are listed among professional writers - mostly at the end of the list (showing relevance to the song). And the list contains from 5 to 12 writers per song. So does any contribution mean they write their own songs? I hope this helps ",
