            },
            "answer_text": "Yes they do. But they also get help from their CEO, Bang Si Hyuk or more we\u2019ll known as Bang PD or Hitman Bang. They also sometimes get help from a producer called Pdogg. His real name is Gang Hyowon and he\u2019s one of the main producers at BigHit. There\u2019s also a man that goes by the name of Slow Rabbit who helped BTS in the beginning. He helped RM and V produce \u20184 O\u2019 Clock\u2019 and helped RM and Suga on their mixtapes. However BTS collaborate and work with so many other artists on various songs but more than 90% of the lyrics are written by BTS themselves according to Pdogg: \u201cI mostly work on making the track and I play the role of completing the lyrics and melody written by the members. More than 90% of the lyrics are written by the members themselves.\u201d - Pdogg For example, J-Hope worked with Supreme Boi on one of his tracks on his Mixtape, Hope World, and he featured in it too. The track was \u201c\ud56d\uc0c1 (HANGSANG)\u201d Amongst BTS themselves, the main producers for their songs are the rap line: J-Hope, Suga and RM. Anyway, in conclusion, yes. BTS do write their own music but often collaborate and work with other producers or artists on some songs. ",
